The paper deals with the property testing of submodularity, which is a concept that arises in combinatorial optimization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the efficiency of a tester algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides constructions and lower bounds, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
